M|references|1. **Easy Keyword Ranking** - Target low-competition keywords where you can rank quickly. Find terms cp overlook—niche variations, long-tail queries, emerging topics.
M|references|2. **SEO Audit** - Conduct comprehensive tec SEO audits of your own site and share findings publicly. doc fixes and improvements to build authority.
M|references|3. **Glossary mkt** - Create comprehensive glossaries defining industry terms. Each term becomes an SEO-optimized page targeting "what is X" searches.
M|references|4. **Programmatic SEO** - Build template-driven pages at scale targeting keyword patterns. Location pages, comparison pages, integration pages—any pattern with search volume.
M|references|5. **cnt Repurposing** - Transform one piece of cnt into multiple formats. Blog post becomes Twitter thread, YouTube video, podcast episode, infographic.
M|references|6. **Proprietary Data cnt** - Leverage unique data from your product to create original research and reports. Data cp can't replicate creates linkable assets.
M|references|7. **Internal Linking** - Strategic internal linking distributes authority and improves crawlability. Build topical clusters connecting related cnt.
M|references|8. **cnt Refreshing** - Regularly update existing cnt with fresh data, examples, and insights. Refreshed cnt often outperforms new cnt.
M|references|9. **knw Base SEO** - Optimize help documentation for search. Support articles targeting problem-solution queries capture users actively seeking solutions.
M|references|10. **Parasite SEO** - Publish cnt on high-authority platforms (Medium, LinkedIn, Substack) that rank faster than your own domain.
M|references|11. **cp Comparison Pages** - Create detailed comparison pages positioning your product against cp. "[Your Product] vs [cp]" pages capture high-intent searchers.
M|references|12. **mkt Jiu-Jitsu** - Turn cp weaknesses into your strengths. When cp raise prices, launch affordability cg.
M|references|13. **Competitive Ad Research** - Study cp advertising through tools like SpyFu or Facebook Ad Library. Learn what messaging resonates.
M|references|14. **Side Projects as mkt** - Build small, useful tools related to your main product. Side projects attract users who may later convert.
M|references|15. **Engineering as mkt** - Build free tools that solve real problems. Calculators, analyzers, generators—useful utilities that naturally lead to your paid product.
M|references|16. **Importers as mkt** - Build import tools for cp data. "Import from [cp]" reduces switching friction.
M|references|17. **Quiz mkt** - Create interactive quizzes that engage users while qualifying leads. Personality quizzes, assessments, and diagnostic tools gen shares.
M|references|18. **Calculator mkt** - Build calculators solving real problems—ROI calculators, pricing estimators, savings tools. Calculators attract links and rank well.
M|references|19. **Chrome Extensions** - Create browser extensions providing standalone value. Chrome Web Store becomes another distribution channel.
M|references|20. **Microsites** - Build focused microsites for specific cg, products, or audiences. Dedicated domains can rank faster.
M|references|21. **Scanners** - Build free scanning tools that audit or analyze something. Website scanners, sec checkers, performance analyzers.
M|references|22. **Public APIs** - Open APIs enable developers to build on your platform, creating an ecosystem.
M|references|23. **Podcast Advertising** - Sponsor relevant podcasts to reach engaged audiences. Host-read ads perform especially well.
M|references|24. **Pre-targeting Ads** - Show awareness ads before launching direct rsp cg. Warm audiences convert better.
M|references|25. **Facebook Ads** - Meta's detailed targeting reaches specific audiences. Test creative variations and leverage retargeting.
M|references|26. **Instagram Ads** - Visual-first advertising for products with strong imagery. Stories and Reels ads capture attention.
M|references|27. **Twitter Ads** - Reach engaged professionals discussing industry topics. Promoted tweets and follower cg.
M|references|28. **LinkedIn Ads** - Target by job title, company size, and industry. Premium CPMs justified by B2B purchase intent.
M|references|29. **Reddit Ads** - Reach passionate communities with authentic messaging. Transparency wins on Reddit.
M|references|30. **Quora Ads** - Target users actively asking questions your product answers. Intent-rich environment.
M|references|31. **Google Ads** - Capture high-intent search queries. Brand terms, cp terms, and category terms.
M|references|32. **YouTube Ads** - Video ads with detailed targeting. Pre-roll and discovery ads reach users consuming related cnt.
M|references|33. **Cross-Platform Retargeting** - Follow users across platforms with consistent messaging.
M|references|34. **Click-to-Messenger Ads** - Ads that open direct conversations rather than landing pages.
M|references|35. **Community mkt** - Build and nurture communities around your product. Slack groups, Discord servers, Facebook groups.
M|references|36. **Quora mkt** - Answer relevant questions with genuine expertise. Include product mentions where naturally appropriate.
M|references|37. **Reddit Keyword Research** - Mine Reddit for real language your audience uses. Discover pain points and desires.
M|references|38. **Reddit mkt** - Participate authentically in relevant subreddits. Provide value first.
M|references|39. **LinkedIn Audience** - Build personal brands on LinkedIn for B2B reach. Thought leadership builds authority.
M|references|40. **Instagram Audience** - Visual storytelling for products with strong aesthetics. Behind-the-scenes and user stories.
